description: Ireland's chief medical officer Dr Tony Holohan said the Republic has "suppressed Covid-19 as a country".
title: Coronavirus: No new deaths in Republic of Ireland
title_page: Coronavirus: No new deaths in Republic of Ireland - BBC News
maintext: The chief medical officer said that although the recording of no new Covid-19-related deaths has not been seen since mid-March, there is always a "weekend effect" in terms of reporting and believes that this can result in delays.
